82e7bef6-9e65-429e-9a1f-dbb31ecfd6db.06862bb2-16be-4314-96e5-9afecb30eb7b.transition.description=Creating IO service failed 82e7bef6-9e65-429e-9a1f-dbb31ecfd6db.19844db7-41f6-4c54-bdae-867450eb0c84.description=
This subflow was created by the Web Services Wizard to invoke the powerOnLogicalServers operation on https\://tufnellpark\:51443/hpio/controller/soap/v2?wsdl. Note that the inputs to this flow which correspond to web service inputs are optional inputs.  This is due to the fact that web services definitions usually incorrectly indicate that too many inputs are required, and mirroring those settings in the flow would force you to enter unused values when running the flow.  The xmlTemplate input on the Invoke Method 2 step of this flow contains a template of the xml message to be sent, and the fields preceded by the comment "<\!--Optional\:-->" or "<\!--zero or more repetitions-->" are those which the web service indicates are optional; all others are indicated to be required.

Inputs\:
host - The host that is running the web service
port - The port on the host running the web service
logicalServerNames0 - The input named powerOnLogicalServers|0|logicalServerNames of the complex type\: powerOnLogicalServers|0
serviceName - The input named powerOnLogicalServers|serviceName of the complex type\: powerOnLogicalServers

Responses\:
success - The SOAP command was accepted by the web service
failure - Something went wrong while making the SOAP request

Extra Results\:
document - The raw XML response of the web service
documentStripped - The XML response of the web service stripped of namespaces
requestId - The output given by the XPath\: /Envelope/Body/powerOnLogicalServersResponse/requestId/text()
82e7bef6-9e65-429e-9a1f-dbb31ecfd6db.268a9bf8-8570-4e25-ae85-f82f377c7af7.description=

Inputs\:
    variablename  - The name of the flow variable where the result should be stored.
Default value\: IC_ReportURL

Default\: "Run History Report Available Here"

Results\:
    result - The untagged URL to the run report for the current run.
Example (with default values)\: IC_ReportURL ,Run History Report Available Here

Responses\:
    success - The flow completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The flow completed unsuccessfully.

Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 82e7bef6-9e65-429e-9a1f-dbb31ecfd6db.6b289351-88fc-4093-a22d-45bde27fb304.description=
Sends an smtp email
 
Input Parameters\:
hostname - hostname or ip address of smtp server
port - port smtp service is listening
from - from email address
to - email address(s) or recipients
subject - email subject
body - body of the email
htmlEmail - true or false, whether the email should be sent supporting html rich email.
readReceipt - true or false, whether or not to request a read receipt
attachments - comma separated list of files to attach (must be full path)
username - if SMTP authentication is needed, the username to send
password - the password to use
characterSet - the character set encoding for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is UTF-8
contentTransferEncoding - the content transfer encoding scheme (such as 7bit, 8bit, base64, quoted-printable etc) for the entire email which includes subject, body, attached file name and the attached file. Default value is - quoted-printable or Q Encoding.
 
 Responses\:
 success - successfully sent the email
 failure - failed to send the email

Note\:
For special characters (East Asian, right-to-left languages, etc.) you must install the support files on your local machine.
	For doing this on Windows go to Control Panel -> Regional and Language Options -> Language and check the options at Supplemental language support.
